title: Princess Eugenie's wedding plans put on hold amid damp row | Daily Mail Online
text: Share this article Share The couple have been dating for six years, and Eugenie has been pictured wearing a ring on her wedding finger, fueling speculation they are engaged. A source told the Sunday Express that the 26-year-old and her family do not want to pay for the repairs by themselves. 'At the moment it’s a stand-off and the whole thing is in limbo,' the insider told the paper. Maintenance work at Kensington Palace usually goes ahead with a number of properties at once in an attempt to keep costs down and despite some alleged heated discussion, there is no wiggle room with Ivy Cottage. The source added: 'Something will have to give soon if Eugenie and Jack are to move in quickly.' Couple: Eugenie leaves Loulou's members club in Mayfair last night with long-term beau Jack Brooksbank, who could be in line for an aristocratic title Princess Eugenie appeared to be wearing a ring on her engagement finger but has denied rumours of an engagement Uncertainty remains about Eugenie's marital status after she was seen wearing a ring on her engagement finger as she left Mayfair private members' club LouLous with boyfriend Jack Brooksbank, 30, back in December. A source close to Eugenie denied to MailOnline that she was engaged, however. ‘There is most definitely no engagement,’ they said. They added: ‘The ring is one that she often wears’. Eugenie, 26, has been in a relationship with nightclub boss Brooksbank for the past six years. Mr Brooksbank's visit to Balmoral last year to meet her grandmother the Queen led to claims he asked Her Majesty for her blessing for a forthcoming engagement - but this was later denied by the couple. If Beatrice or Eugenie have children with non-aristocrats or non-royals then their offspring will be without title, which Prince Andrew does not want, it was claimed in December. Buckingham Palace declined to comment. Read more:
